│                                                                          │
│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                              │
│                                                                          │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                          │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                              │
│ The crash occurs due to an assertion failure in                          │
│ BoUpSLP::ScheduleData::incrementUnscheduledDeps: "hasValidDependencies() │
│ && 'increment of unscheduled deps would be meaningless'". This means     │
│ incrementUnscheduledDeps is being called on a ScheduleData whose         │
│ Dependencies is InvalidDeps. The call stack shows it happens during      │
│ BlockScheduling::schedule when handling readiness checks for control     │
│ dependencies.                                                            │
│                                                                          │
│ 2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log:                                                │
│ The debug log shows scheduling of bundles and then handling different    │
│ dependency kinds:                                                        │
│ - def-use deps (operands)                                                │
│ - memory deps                                                            │
│ - control deps                                                           │
│                                                                          │
│ The critical part is:                                                    │
│ "SLP:   check for readiness (ctrl): %call = tail call i32 (ptr, ...)     │
│ @printf(ptr null, i32 %add1)"                                            │
│ followed immediately by the assertion. In the code, control dependencies │
│ are processed via DecrUnsched(Dep, /*IsControl=*/true). The lambda       │
│ DecrUnsched contains a condition that allows decrementing even if        │
│ hasValidDependencies() is false when IsControl is true:                  │
│                                                                          │
│   if ((IsControl || Data->hasValidDependencies()) &&                     │
│       Data->incrementUnscheduledDeps(-1) == 0) { ... }                   │
│                                                                          │
│ This directly contradicts incrementUnscheduledDeps' assertion requiring  │
│ valid dependencies.                                                      │
│                                                                          │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                  │
│ - ScheduleData::incrementUnscheduledDeps asserts hasValidDependencies(). │
│ - DecrUnsched allows calling incrementUnscheduledDeps when IsControl is  │
│ true, regardless of dependency validity, presumably to handle certain    │
│ control dep scenarios.                                                   │
│ - This mismatch causes the assertion to fire when a control dependency   │
│ has not yet had its dependency count initialized.                        │
│ - The design intent elsewhere: ScheduleData::clearDirectDependencies     │
│ retains memory/control deps but sets Dependencies to InvalidDeps and     │
│ resets UnscheduledDeps, meaning control/memory deps should only be       │
│ decremented after their dependency counts are initialized. The           │
│ permissive DecrUnsched path violates this.                               │
│                                                                          │
│ Therefore, the bug is that DecrUnsched should not call                   │
│ incrementUnscheduledDeps unless hasValidDependencies() is true, even for │
│ control dependencies.                                                    │
│                                                                          │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s)                                                │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                  │
│ - Location: In BlockScheduling::schedule(), within the lambda            │
│ DecrUnsched defined around lines 5401-5434.                              │
│ - Change the condition from `(IsControl ||                               │
│ Data->hasValidDependencies())` to `Data->hasValidDependencies()` so that │
│ we never call incrementUnscheduledDeps unless the dependency info is     │
│ valid. This aligns with the assertion and avoids crashing.               │
│                                                                          │
│ Edit:                                                                    │
│ Replace:                                                                 │
│   if ((IsControl || Data->hasValidDependencies()) &&                     │
│       Data->incrementUnscheduledDeps(-1) == 0) {                         │
│ with:                                                                    │
│   if (Data->hasValidDependencies() &&                                    │
│       Data->incrementUnscheduledDeps(-1) == 0) {                         │
│                                                                          │
│ This ensures control dependencies are only decremented when their        │
│ dependency counters have been computed, consistent with the invariant    │
│ enforced by incrementUnscheduledDeps.                                    │
│                                                                          │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                           │
│ The crash stems from a logical inconsistency: allowing decrement of      │
│ unscheduled dependencies for control deps without ensuring dependency    │
│ info is valid. Tightening DecrUnsched to require hasValidDependencies    │
│ for all cases prevents calling incrementUnscheduledDeps on invalid data, │
│ satisfying the assertion and preserving scheduler invariants. This fix   │
│ avoids the abort without altering scheduling semantics, since readiness  │
│ must be based on correctly initialized dependency counts.                │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                          │
│                                                                          │
